SIMPLE: pleurisy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pleurisy
<hw>Pleu"ri*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pleur⟦eacute⟧sie</ets>, L. <ets>pleurisis</ets>,
<ets>pleuritis</ets>, Gr <grk>pleyri^tis</grk> (sc. <grk>no`sos</grk>),
fr. <grk>pleyra`</grk> rib, side.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
inflammation of the pleura, usually accompanied with fever, pain,
difficult respiration, and cough, and with exudation into the pleural
cavity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pleurisy root</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<cd>The large tuberous root of a kind of milkweed (<spn>Asclepias
tuberosa</spn>) which is used as a remedy for pleuritic and other
diseases</cd>. <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The plant itself, which has deep
orange-colored flowers; -- called also <altname>butterfly
weed</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pleurite</ent>⟦br⟧
